        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/default.png"
      },
      {
        "position": 5,
        "title": "Writing this in case someone has this issue...",
        "text": "I'm posting the email I sent to Garmin:I purchased the Garmin Alpha LTE collar and received it on 11.18.2024.It was required that I download and install the Garmin App for Android (which I did).It was also required that I subscribe to the LTE plan (which I did).I confirmed it is the latest version of the APP and that the collar was updated.Unfortunately the APP persistently crashes and is unusable. I immediately cancelled the LTE subscription (within an hour) and set up a return of the collar as it is unusable.However, I do not see a refund on my credit card, nor do I see a receipt for same.Please advise...Garmin got right back to me over email and refunded the subscription. I am VERY VERY impressed with their support. A+That said the APP has like 2 stars on Play Store (which I didn't realize) so...Anyway, hope this helps someone :-)",
        "rating": 1,
        "date": "November 19, 2024",
