      {
        "position": 8,
        "title": "Total toss up - sometimes it works perfectly and sometimes it’s useless",
        "text": "Sometimes the tracking is accurate and consistent with little to no time delay. Sometimes you get a “Server error” message on the app and nothing works. Sometimes it says the dog is in one place for hours when the dog has been elsewhere the whole time. Sometimes it shows the dog in place for an extended period of time and then suddenly it’ll catch up and show the entire track and correct location on the app. I have no idea of this tracker will work when I need it to work. Sometimes it does work great and is perfect. Sometimes it does not function. For reference it is being used on a young herding dog on a large farm. I cannot figure out why it works great sometimes and is completely useless other times when used in the same location. This tracker costs WAY too much to function so inconsistently.",
